        },
        {
          "title": "The long pasuk in Tzav and the short pasuk in Kedoshim regarding piggul and notar",
          "display_title": "Long & Short Pesukim",
          "timestamp": "00:44"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Rava's Comprehensive Derivation of Piggul Halachot from the Pasuk in Tzav",
      "display_title": "Rava's Derivation",
      "timestamp": "02:46",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rava's opening: all piggul halachot from the long pasuk in Tzav",
          "display_title": "All from Tzav",
          "timestamp": "02:46"
        },
        {
          "title": "The double language of He'achol Ye'achel and two types of eating",
          "display_title": "Double Language",
          "timestamp": "03:06"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Rava's Comprehensive Derivation of Piggul Halachot from the Pasuk in Tzav (continued)",
      "display_title": "Rava's Derivation…",
      "timestamp": "03:59",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Why shelamim are the paradigm and what is excluded",
          "display_title": "Shelamim Paradigm",
          "timestamp": "03:59"
        },
        {
          "title": "Piggul on the third day as chutz lizmano; lo yiratzeh and hartzaat kasher vs. hartzaat pasul",
          "display_title": "Shlishi & Hartzaah",
          "timestamp": "05:59"
        },
        {
          "title": "Everything must be done correctly except for the piggul thought; hartzaat pasul requires all matirim",
          "display_title": "Matirim & Process",
          "timestamp": "06:41"
        },
        {
          "title": "The time of piggul is during hakrava, not retroactively on shlishi",
          "display_title": "Time of Piggul",
          "timestamp": "08:24"
        },
        {
          "title": "Lo yechashev lo: other thoughts invalidate, splitting of kavana between chutz lizmano and chutz limkomo",
          "display_title": "Lo Yechashev",
          "timestamp": "09:17"
        },
        {
          "title": "Yihyeh teaches combining: half kezayit of each type of piggul thought combines for invalidation",
          "display_title": "Yihyeh & Combining",
          "timestamp": "10:40"
        },
        {
          "title": "Mimenu from it singular: only one of them receives karet",
          "display_title": "Mimenu Singular",
          "timestamp": "11:23"
        },
        {
          "title": "Chutz lizmano gets karet: learned via gezeirah shavah avon-avon from notar in the parallel pasuk",
          "display_title": "Chutz Lizmano Karet",
          "timestamp": "12:02"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Introduction and Overview of Piggul Sources in the Pessukim (continued)",
      "display_title": "Piggul Sources…",
      "timestamp": "03:59",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Why shelamim serves as the paradigm for piggul: maphalgin umitpalgin principle",
          "display_title": "Shelamim Paradigm",
          "timestamp": "03:59"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Rav Pappa's Challenge and the Role of the Pasuk in Kedoshim: Makom Meshulash",
      "display_title": "Rav Pappa & Kedoshim",
      "timestamp": "13:40",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rav Pappa's challenge: what does the pasuk in Kedoshim teach that wasn't in Tzav?",
          "display_title": "Rav Pappa's Q",
          "timestamp": "13:40"
        },
        {
          "title": "The makom meshulash requirement: place equal for dam, basar, and imurim",
          "display_title": "Makom Meshulash",
          "timestamp": "14:03"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rashi's interpretation: heichal is not makom meshulash for all three",
          "display_title": "Rashi Heichal",
          "timestamp": "14:30"
        },
        {
          "title": "Tosafot explanations: bazavach offering, person standing in place",
          "display_title": "Tosafot Views",
          "timestamp": "16:19"
        },
        {
          "title": "Why Tzav alone could not teach makom meshulash without Kedoshim pasuk",
          "display_title": "Need for Kedoshim",
          "timestamp": "18:32"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Baraitot on Piggul: Dispute Regarding Retroactivity and the Role of Machshava",
      "display_title": "Baraitot Disputes",
      "timestamp": "20:16",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Eliezer: piggul is about machshava of eating on shlishi, not retroactive invalidation",
          "display_title": "R. Eliezer View",
          "timestamp": "20:16"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Akiva's objection: examples of retroactive invalidation from zav and zavah, shomeret yom kineged yom",
          "display_title": "R. Akiva Tzad",
          "timestamp": "21:31"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Eliezer's response: hamakriv oto shows invalidation occurs at time of hakrava, not retroactively",
          "display_title": "R. Eliezer Response",
          "timestamp": "24:07"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ben Azzai: oto teaches it is only this case, not bal te'acher",
          "display_title": "Ben Azzai Oto",
          "timestamp": "25:15"
        },
        {
          "title": "Acherim say: lo yechashev shows invalidation through machshava, not on shlishi",
          "display_title": "Acherim View",
          "timestamp": "26:17"
        },
        {
          "title": "Gemara on Ben Azzai and oto; lo yiratzeh and hartzaat kasher teach it is the korban not the kohen",
          "display_title": "Korban Not Kohen",
          "timestamp": "26:42"
        },
        {
          "title": "Gemara on whether Ben Azzai learns bal te'acher from oto or from gezeirah shavah of avon-avon with notar",
          "display_title": "Ben Azzai Source",
          "timestamp": "28:14"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rav Ashi: why Ben Azzai needs both oto and the gezeirah about bechor and ma'aser",
          "display_title": "Rav Ashi Why Both",
          "timestamp": "30:12"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ben Azzai teaches oto for kodashim that are bnei hartza'ah not just for bechor",
          "display_title": "Kodashim Hartza'ah",
          "timestamp": "31:35"
        },
        {
          "title": "Gemara: why also need oto when ve'haya becha cheit velo b'korbanacha cheit teaches it?",
          "display_title": "Why Oto Needed",
          "timestamp": "32:34"
        },
        {
          "title": "Discussion of wife's death for non-payment of neder; ain ishto shel adam meta principle",
          "display_title": "Wife Death Neder",
          "timestamp": "33:13"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rav Ashi and Rav Mari: machshevet kodashim teaches you get malkaot",
          "display_title": "Malkaot Taught",
          "timestamp": "37:51"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rav Ashi to Rav Mari: lav she'ein bo ma'aseh eino lokah",
          "display_title": "Lav Lo Ma'aseh",
          "timestamp": "38:24"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rav Mari: follows Rabbi Yehudah that you get malkaot even without ma'aseh",
          "display_title": "R. Yehudah Malkaot",
          "timestamp": "38:40"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Mishnah: The Four Avodot of Blood and the Conditions for Piggul and Psul",
      "display_title": "Mishnah Four Avodot",
      "timestamp": "38:57",
      "micro_segments": [
        {
          "title": "Zeh haklal: shochet, makabel, mehalech, zorek—four acts where piggul thought applies",
          "display_title": "Four Avodot",
          "timestamp": "38:57"
        },
        {
          "title": "Kavana requirements: eating thing normally eaten, burning thing normally burned, kezayit minimum",
          "display_title": "Kavana Requirements",
          "timestamp": "39:05"
        },
        {
          "title": "Chutz limkomo: psul, no karet",
          "display_title": "Chutz Limkomo",
          "timestamp": "39:48"
        },
        {
          "title": "Chutz lizmano: piggul, karet applies",
          "display_title": "Chutz Lizmano",
          "timestamp": "39:54"
        },
        {
          "title": "Condition: matir must be brought kemitzvato properly",
          "display_title": "Matir Kemitzvato",
          "timestamp": "40:15"
        },
        {
          "title": "Example of kemitzvato: one proper thought, rest with chutz lizmano thoughts",
          "display_title": "Kemitzvato Example",
          "timestamp": "40:46"
        },
        {
          "title": "Examples of lo karav matir kemitzvato: additional invalidating thoughts mix in",
          "display_title": "Lo Karav Examples",
          "timestamp": "41:24"
        },
        {
          "title": "Case of half kezayit chutz limkomo and half kezayit chutz lizmano: psul not piggul",
          "display_title": "Half Kezayit Mix",
          "timestamp": "44:18"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Yehudah: if chutz lizmano thought comes first, later chutz limkomo does not remove piggul status",
          "display_title": "R. Yehudah First",
          "timestamp": "45:55"
        },
        {
          "title": "Rabbi Yehudah: if chutz limkomo comes first, cannot become piggul; if both mixed, psul",
          "display_title": "R. Yehudah Order",
          "timestamp": "46:44"
        },
        {
          "title": "Chachamim: either way psul, no karet",
          "display_title": "Chachamim View",
          "timestamp": "46:56"
        },
        {
          "title": "Achila and haktara do not combine: half kezayit eating, half kezayit burning are separate",
          "display_title": "No Achila Haktara",
          "timestamp": "47:31"
        }
      ]
    }
